@startuml
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 10

title REQ_BB_01 – Blood Type Alert Operation

actor "Blood_Bank_Manager" as Manager

box "Controller" #LightBlue
  participant AlertController
end box

box "Application" #LightGreen
  participant BloodTypeAlertService
end box

box "Domain" #LightYellow
  participant BloodTypeAlertOperation
  participant BloodTypeResource
  participant User
  participant Permission
  participant State
end box

box "Infrastructure" #LightCoral
  participant InventoryPort
  participant NotificationPort
end box

box "External" #LightGray
  participant Inventory_API
  participant Email_SMS_Gateway
end box

== Normal Flow (Stock < 5) ==

Manager -> AlertController: POST /alert { bloodTypes } [TLS]
note right of AlertController: Authenticated (Admin permission required)

AlertController -> BloodTypeAlertService: initiateAlert(bloodTypes, manager)

BloodTypeAlertService -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: create(manager, bloodTypes)

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> User: hasPermission(Permission.Admin): boolean
User --> BloodTypeAlertOperation: true

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> BloodTypeResource: isAccessible(manager): boolean
BloodTypeResource --> BloodTypeAlertOperation: true

BloodTypeAlertOperation --> BloodTypeAlertService: validation ok

BloodTypeAlertService -> InventoryPort: getInventoryLevels(bloodTypes) [TLS]
InventoryPort -> Inventory_API: GET /inventory?bloodTypes=... [TLS]
Inventory_API --> InventoryPort: { levels: Map<BloodType, Integer> }
InventoryPort --> BloodTypeAlertService: inventory data

BloodTypeAlertService -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: checkStock(inventory)

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: detect stock < 5 for at least one blood type
BloodTypeAlertOperation --> BloodTypeAlertService: stockLowDetected

BloodTypeAlertService -> NotificationPort: sendAlert(channels: [Email, SMS], message)
note right of NotificationPort: Must use exactly 2 channels (email + SMS)

NotificationPort -> Email_SMS_Gateway: POST /email [TLS]
Email_SMS_Gateway --> NotificationPort: 200 OK

NotificationPort -> Email_SMS_Gateway: POST /sms [TLS]
Email_SMS_Gateway --> NotificationPort: 200 OK

NotificationPort --> BloodTypeAlertService: alerts sent

BloodTypeAlertService -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: updateState(Post1)
BloodTypeAlertOperation -> State: setState(Post1)
State --> BloodTypeAlertOperation: ok
BloodTypeAlertOperation --> BloodTypeAlertService: state changed

BloodTypeAlertService --> AlertController: 200 Alerts sent
AlertController --> Manager: 200 OK

note right of AlertController: Post1 state reached: alert sent

== Error Flow (Stale Data) ==

Manager -> AlertController: POST /alert { bloodTypes } [TLS]
note right of AlertController: Authenticated (Admin permission required)

AlertController -> BloodTypeAlertService: initiateAlert(bloodTypes, manager)

BloodTypeAlertService -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: create(manager, bloodTypes)

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> User: hasPermission(Permission.Admin): boolean
User --> BloodTypeAlertOperation: true

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> BloodTypeResource: isAccessible(manager): boolean
BloodTypeResource --> BloodTypeAlertOperation: true

BloodTypeAlertOperation --> BloodTypeAlertService: validation ok

BloodTypeAlertService -> InventoryPort: getInventoryLevels(bloodTypes) [TLS]
InventoryPort -> Inventory_API: GET /inventory?bloodTypes=... [TLS]
Inventory_API --> InventoryPort: { levels: ..., stale: true }
InventoryPort --> BloodTypeAlertService: inventory data (flagged stale)

BloodTypeAlertService -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: checkStock(inventory)

BloodTypeAlertOperation -> BloodTypeAlertOperation: detect stale flag
note right of BloodTypeAlertOperation: Edge case: stale/incorrect data → no state change
BloodTypeAlertOperation --> BloodTypeAlertService: staleDataDetected

BloodTypeAlertService --> AlertController: 400 Bad Request (stale data)
AlertController --> Manager: 400 Error: Inventory data stale, alert not sent

note right of AlertController: Pre1 state remains (op.post = op.pre)

== Concurrent Stock Drops ==

note right of Manager
  When multiple blood types drop below 5 units simultaneously,
  each drop triggers its own BloodTypeAlertOperation instance.
  Operations are independent and do not interfere.
  The same owner (Inventory_Management_Team) is enforced by the accessible set.
end note
@enduml